DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$x1 = non_zero_random(1,9,1);
$y1 = non_zero_random(1,9,1);
$x2 = non_zero_random(1,9,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Evaluate the expression \( \frac{\sqrt{-$x1}}{\sqrt{-$y1}\sqrt{-$x2}} \) and
write the result in the form \(a+ b i\). 
$BR $BR 
The real number \(a\) equals \{ans_rule(15) \}
$BR
The real number \( b \) equals \{ans_rule(15) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans1 = 0;
$ans2 = sqrt($x1)/(sqrt($y1)*sqrt($x2));
ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(num_cmp($ans2));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.

